<subSubSection id="C306789DFFC6FF976BB0FF59FD8BFEB3" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" type="reference_group">
This is the most common 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC6FF976A9AFF56FD90FF07" authority="Mayr, 1855" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" box="[445,590,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976A9AFF56FD90FF07" box="[445,590,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">Tetramorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species found in the Arabian Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC6FF976F38FF59FB23FF18" author="Collingwood, C. A." box="[1055,1277,151,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood, 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC6FF976E2DFF59FE80FF7D" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D." pageId="12" pageNumber="577" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref6843" refString="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. (1996) Formicidae of Saudi Arabia (Part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 15, 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti, 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC6FF976A4CFF72FD5CFF7D" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. &amp; Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T." box="[363,642,188,213]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" pagination="405 - 474" refId="ref6877" refString="Collingwood, C. A., Agosti, D., Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T. (2011) Order Hymenoptera, Family Formicidae. Arthropod Fauna of the UAE, 4, 405 - 474." type="journal article" year="2011">
Collingwood 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976921FF73FD9FFF7D" box="[518,577,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
) and is also broadly distributed in the savannah of tropical Africa. In Rawdhat Khorim, this species is very common and occurs during all months of the year, with a peak in December. It was observed foraging on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC6FF976AF1FECAFD90FEB4" box="[470,590,260,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976AF1FECAFD90FEB4" box="[470,590,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">C. procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection id="C306789DFFC6FF976BB0FE82FA42FDD5" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" type="key">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC6FF976BB0FE82FC55FE20" blockId="12.[151,1436,332,392]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
In the key to Arabian species (Sharaf 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976968FE83FD54FECD" box="[591,650,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">et al.</emphasis>
2012:7) 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC6FF9769D3FE83FCA0FECD" authorityName="Sharaf &amp; Abdel-Dayem &amp; Al Dhafer &amp; Aldawood" authorityYear="2013" box="[756,894,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saudicum">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF9769D3FE83FCA0FECD" box="[756,894,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">T. saudicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will key to couplet 16 along with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC6FF976E34FE82FAB4FECD" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1911" box="[1299,1386,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chefketi">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976E34FE82FAB4FECD" box="[1299,1386,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">chefketi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976BB0FEBEFF20FE2F" box="[151,254,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">syriacum</emphasis>
. Couplet 16 is modified here to separate the three species.
</paragraph>
<key id="FF8D7C27FFC6FF976BB0FE79FA42FDD5" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
<keyStep id="30E833B3FFC6FF976BB0FE79FA42FDD5" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC6FF976BB0FE79FA42FE42" blockId="12.[151,1437,439,637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
<keyLead id="30ED8823FFC6FF976BB0FE79FA42FE42" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
16. Mesosomal pilosity restricted to pronotum and first half of mesonotum, propodeum bare; SL 0.78–0.87; petiolar and postpetiolar nodes coarsely sulcate (
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC6FF976AC8FE1AFDEFFE42" box="[495,561,468,490]" name="Russia" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">Russia</collectingCountry>
&amp; Arabia)......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC6FF976E6AFE1AFA42FE42" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1911" box="[1357,1436,468,490]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chefketi">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976E6AFE1AFA42FE42" bold="true" box="[1357,1436,468,490]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">chefketi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC6FF976BB0FE3CFA42FD8D" blockId="12.[151,1437,439,637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
<keyLead id="30ED8823FFC6FF976BB0FE3CFA42FD8D" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
- Mesosoma with abundant, stout and relatively long suberect hairs; SL 0.70–0.77; petiolar and postpetiolar nodes irregularly sculptured (Middle East).......................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976E66FDC1FA42FD8D" bold="true" box="[1345,1436,527,549]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">syriacum</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC6FF976BB0FDE3FA42FDD5" blockId="12.[151,1437,439,637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
<keyLead id="30ED8823FFC6FF976BB0FDE3FA42FDD5" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
- Mesosomal pilosity fine and acute apically and restricted to mesonotum, propodeal dorsum with a single pair; SL 0.50–0.55; petiolar node clearly irregularly rugulose; postpetiolar node distinctly strongly longitudinally rugulose (
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC6FF976FE6FD87FA9BFDF7" box="[1217,1349,585,607]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
)............................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976E27FDA9FA42FDD5" bold="true" box="[1280,1436,615,637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC6FF976E27FDA9FABFFDD5" authority="Sharaf &amp; Abdel-Dayem &amp; Al Dhafer &amp; Aldawood, 2013" authorityName="Sharaf &amp; Abdel-Dayem &amp; Al Dhafer &amp; Aldawood" authorityYear="2013" box="[1280,1377,615,637]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saudicum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC6FF976E27FDA9FABFFDD5" bold="true" box="[1280,1377,615,637]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="577">saudicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25B4A7FFFC6FF976E41FDA9FA42FDD5" box="[1382,1436,615,637]" pageId="12" pageNumber="577" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
</subSubSection>
